    "created_at": "2016-07-14T18:12:59Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-14T18:13:51Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This issue is preventing me from using gRPC in my project as stdout/stderr output from a third party library is highly undesirable.  `GRPC_VERBOSITY` is a good start to suppress a number of messages, but some bugs in 0.15.0 appear to cause errors to be printed in simple use cases (such as #7267 which happens for me in C++ clients for shutdown, at least with respect to the `FD shutdown` message).\n\nI would also like to echo the sentiment that general purpose libraries such as gRPC should ideally be opt-in to stdout/stderr writes (_especially_ when defaulting to a debug level), but I'd be satisfied with an opt-out solution provided I can suppress all gRPC stdout/stderr writes.\n"
  },
